n now schedules a server-side push send, and deep links of the form `codeforge-mobile://project/<id>` are handled to route into the project screen.

Critical findings / analysis:
- ✅ Backend support is additive and aligned with scope: new `userPushTokens` table, `users.registerPushToken` mutation, internal token query, and internal action to send Expo pushes.
- ✅ Build completion hook is correctly attached in `buildLoop.finishSession` and only triggers for `completed` status.
- ✅ Mobile app config includes notification plugin + dependency; root layout requests permission and registers Expo token after auth.
- ✅ Deep link parsing and navigation are implemented for both initial URL and runtime URL events.
- ⚠️ The local “build complete while screen open” notification logic in `app/project/[id].tsx` likely never fires as intended: it watches `buildLoop.getActiveSession`, which returns only `running` sessions and then `null` once completed, so a `running -> completed` transition is not observable via that query.
- ⚠️ New `router.push(... as any)` casts were introduced in deep-link handling. This is non-blocking but should be tightened to typed route-safe navigation to avoid masking routing/type issues.

Security: none observed (no serious authz/injection/secret handling regressions in this diff).

Next actions:
1) Fix the in-screen completion detection (e.g., query latest session status rather than only active-running session, or remove this local notification path if server push is the intended sole mechanism).
2) Replace new `as any` route casts with typed-safe route construction.
